ition at theParis Olympics.\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 520, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 402, \"end\": 417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999989500289358, \"rank\": 1.0499721319899203e-06, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the format\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 445}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 track and field competition\", \"from\": 462, \"to\": 498}, {\"ngram\": \"theParis Olympics\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 519}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The specifics are pretty simple.\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 554, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The specifics\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 535}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic track and field athletes who do not automatically qualify through the first round of action in the 200m, 400m, 800m, 1,500m, 100mH, 110mH and 400mH will be granted an additional round to secure their spots into the semifinals.\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 790, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic track and field athletes\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 588}, {\"ngram\": \"the first round\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 645}, {\"ngram\": \"action\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 655}, {\"ngram\": \"the 200m\", \"from\": 659, \"to\": 667}, {\"ngram\": \"400m\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 673}, {\"ngram\": \"800m\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 679}, {\"ngram\": \"1,500m\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 687}, {\"ngram\": \"100mH\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 694}, {\"ngram\": \"110mH\", \"from\": 696, \"to\": 701}, {\"ngram\": \"400mH\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 711}, {\"ngram\": \"an additional round\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 747}, {\"ngram\": \"their spots\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 769}, {\"ngram\": \"the semifinals\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 789}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes who automatically qualify through to the semifinals will continue their medal